Route Service Cloud Messaging Sessions to Queues

You can route customer messages sent over Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, Apple Messages for Business, or SMS to the appropriate queue using an Omni-Channel routing configuration.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions
This article applies to: Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create or change queues: Customize Application and Manage Public List Views
To set up and edit Messaging channels: Configure Messaging
To view channels: View Setup and Configuration

Set Up Queue-Based Routing for a New Messaging Channel
Create the channel and queue-based routing at the same time. Create a new queue, create a routing configuration, adjust the agent messaging workload, and exit the setup flow.

Set Up Queue-Based Routing for an Existing Messaging Channel
Enable Omni-Channel, configure the other options, save your changes, create a service channel, create presence statuses, create an Omni-Channel queue, associate your routing configuration and agents with the queue, edit the properties in the Routing section, and select the queue that receives and prioritizes this channel's messaging sessions.
